This is code for the THERMAL FLASHLIGHT project, part of the Public Laboratory for Open Technology and Science. (http://publiclaboratory.org)

It is open source, free software, and is available under the MIT license (see LICENSE in this directory)

Update! Now, this is a Glowdoodle (http://scripts.mit.edu/~eric_r/glowdoodle/) esque light painting app, created for the Thermal Flashlight project, which allows you (if you have a thermal flashlight) to generate an image of 'heat'. Read more about the project here: http://publiclaboratory.org/tools/thermal-photography

/thermographer-website/ is an IN PROGRESS/ALPHA Ruby on Rails 3.0 (Ruby 1.9.2) web application for online interpretation and publication of your thermal infrared photos.

----

Old! Ignore: 

/control-code/ contains the code to drive the old thermographer hardware. It runs on Arduino (http://arduino.cc)

To save output from the camera on Linux or Mac OS X, run the command:

screen -L /dev/ttyUSB* 9600

and when you're done, press control-a, then the letter h. This will save a copy of the readout.

